  "body": "When running an erigon node with Kurtosis (don't know if the problem is present with erigon on local) , erigon print the enode address like this : \r\n\r\n`Started P2P networking version=67 self=enode://849ec16e873c3bedaad5cd948391e7001b8eff0b7ccd5974597b2e1b47ffcaefdd311b93c2b1176463550e206abe8d7a3606424dc22babbb0e5924b6b9b8a2c2@172.16.0.9:0 name=erigon/v2.49.0-dev-8983128d/linux-amd64/go1.20.7`\r\n\r\nthe enode displayed have the ip 172.16.0.9:0 . The port 0 is incorrect and should be 30303 .\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n- [Install and run kurtosis with an erigon node](https://docs.kurtosis.com/how-to-local-eth-testnet)\r\n- check the logs of erigon\r\n",
